# Line-ending policy: this repo is LF-only.
#
# Developed on WSL/Linux and deployed to Unix/AWS, so every text file is
# stored AND checked out as LF. The practical payoff: if an editor ever
# saves a file with Windows CRLF endings, Git normalizes it away instead of
# treating it as a modification — so a stray CRLF can never block a branch
# checkout or stash the way it did before this file existed.

# Auto-detect text vs binary; normalize all text to LF in the repo and on checkout.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Belt-and-suspenders for files that break with CRLF even on a Windows checkout.
# (Redundant with the rule above today, but explicit so it survives any future
#  softening of the '*' line.)
*.sh   text eol=lf
*.bash text eol=lf
